# When consecutive fields have differently-shaped composite keys
# (different braceless-chain lengths), the alignment table is flushed
# so values only align within runs of same-shape keys. Here the first
# two rows have two-level chains and align together; the third row has
# a three-level chain and is rendered without joining that group.
-- in.cue --
aa: bb: 1
c: d: 2
eee: f: g: 3
-- out/relpos --
aa: bb: 1
c: d:   2
eee: f: g: 3
-- out/norelpos --
aa: bb: 1, c: d: 2, eee: f: g: 3
